tations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11644/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11644/canvas/1/a8653ca0-4a00-473d-8096-e211c99e0547","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T20:09:41.369Z","creator":"lucia","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The seamstresses are shot from a low angle, as if we are seeing them through Cyril’s eyes, from her seated position at the desk. The angle also gives the viewer the sense that the women are looming over her. Though the women themselves are not intimidating to Cyril, the news they carry is disastrous and shocking, and carries serious consequences.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11644/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:342.39067055393593,103.38192419825064,1414.3440233236151,959.067055393586"}}}]}]}]}